k=n.yr("All trading data displayed in VIB3 Trades is sourced from publicly available filings with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC), including congressional STOCK Act disclosures and institutional 13F holdings reports.\n\nThis data is public information and does NOT constitute insider information. Public filings may be delayed by days, weeks, or months from the actual transaction date. Market conditions may change significantly between the time a trade was executed and when it was publicly disclosed.\n\nWe make reasonable efforts to ensure accuracy, but we do not guarantee that all data is complete, current, or error-free.",B.hm,B.az,"SEC Disclosure")
s=n.yr("In accordance with FINRA guidelines:\n\nPAST PERFORMANCE DOES NOT GUARANTEE FUTURE RESULTS. The fact that a politician, hedge fund manager, or institutional investor made a profitable trade does not mean that copying that trade will produce the same results.\n\nThe value of investments can go down as well as up. You may receive back less than your original investment. Different types of investments involve varying degrees of risk, and there can be no assurance that any specific investment or strategy will be profitable.\n\nHistorical returns, expected returns, and probability projections are provided for informational purposes and may not reflect actual future performance.",B.ec,B.p,"FINRA Investment Risks")
r=n.yr("Copy-trading carries additional risks beyond standard market risks:\n\nExecution Delays: There is a time gap between when a public filing is disclosed and when your copy-trade is executed. Market prices may move significantly during this period.\n\nPrice Slippage: The price at which your trade executes may differ materially from the price in the original filing. This is especially true for illiquid securities or during volatile market conditions.\n\nPosition Size Differences: Institutional investors and politicians may have vastly different portfolio sizes, risk tolerances, and investment horizons than individual retail investors.\n\nPartial Information: Public filings only show a snapshot of an investor's activity. You may not see their full portfolio, hedging strategies, or other positions that offset risk.",B.ll,B.Z,"Copy-Trading Risks")
q=n.yr("VIB3 Trades makes NO guarantee of investment returns. We do not promise, predict, or imply that you will earn profits or avoid losses by using the App.\n\nAny performance data, backtest results, or hypothetical scenarios shown within the App are for illustrative purposes only and do not represent actual trading results. Simulated or backtested performance has inherent limitations and does not reflect the impact of actual market conditions.",B.UL,B.q,"No Guarantee of Returns")
p=n.yr("VIB3 Trades, Inc. is NOT a registered broker-dealer, investment advisor, or financial institution. We do not hold, manage, or have custody of your funds or securities.\n\nAll trading is executed through your connected third-party brokerage accounts. Your broker is responsible for trade execution, settlement, and regulatory compliance. Brokerage services are provided by:\n\n  - Alpaca Securities LLC, member FINRA/SIPC\n  - Coinbase, Inc., licensed money transmitter\n  - Interactive Brokers LLC, member FINRA/SIPC/NYSE\n\nSecurities in your brokerage account are protected by SIPC up to $500,000 (including $250,000 for cash claims) through your broker. SIPC does not protect against market losses.\n\nIf you have questions about the regulatory status of any service, please consult FINRA BrokerCheck (brokercheck.finra.org) or the SEC's EDGAR database (sec.gov/edgar).",B.UY,B.x,"Regulatory Notice")
